@smeylan is this what you were thinking of?

Fixes #5685 and adds integration tests to prevent regressions.

The issue is now we sometimes use an `AuthHandler` instance multiple times when previously it was only used once. Continuously adding to the list of authorizations and trying to solve the challenges again makes boulder mad (it errors saying we're trying to modify a failed challenge), so let's limit the scope of `aauthzrs` to the `handle_authorizations` method.

@ohemorange, if you have time to quickly review this, it's valuable as you're the most familiar with the changes here, but if not @joohoi, it'd be great if you could take a look. All we should be changing is we now pass the variable around rather than keeping it on the class and adding tests so it should be pretty straightforward.
